@startuml AC-05_SQL_Injection

title AC-05 — SQL Injection via Application Input Modifies Database Records\nSTRIDE: Tampering | Severity: Critical | Mitigation: M-05

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Operator / Customer\n(Legitimate)" as user #DDEEFF
actor "External Attacker /\nMalicious Operator" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Search Products or\nMachines via API" as UC5 << normal >>
  usecase "Detect Injectable\nParameter (error-based)" as AC5a << abuse >>
  usecase "Inject SQL to Modify\nMySQL Records Directly" as AC5 << abuse >>
  usecase "Escalate Privilege /\nErase Audit Trail" as AC5b << abuse >>
}

user --> UC5

attacker --> AC5a
AC5a ..> AC5  : <<enables>>
AC5 ..> UC5   : <<threatens>>
AC5 ..> AC5b  : <<extends>>

note right of AC5
  **Preconditions:**
  • At least one endpoint uses Hibernate
    native query with string concatenation
  • Application DB account holds DML
    privileges (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE)
  • Error responses confirm injectable param
  • Attacker holds any valid JWT (or none
    if endpoint is unprotected)
end note

note right of AC5b
  **Impact:**
  Integrity: arbitrary DML on any table —
  roles modified, prices zeroed, sale records
  deleted, audit entries removed
  Confidentiality: UNION SELECT / INTO OUTFILE
  Business: irreversible data corruption,
  regulatory liability for lost audit trail
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vectors:**
  Probe: {"name":"Juice'"}  → MySQL syntax error
  Privilege escalation:
    name=Juice'; UPDATE users SET role='ADMINISTRATOR'
    WHERE username='attacker';--
  Destroy evidence:
    name=Juice'; DELETE FROM sale WHERE created_at < NOW();--
end note

@enduml
